conformanceStatements.description: The value of ORC-2 (Placer Order Number) SHALL be identical to the value of OBR-2 (Placer Order Number) within the same Order_Observation Group instance.
conformanceStatements.assertion:
<Assertion xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">
						<FORALL>
							<PathValue Operator="EQ" Path1="1[1].2[1].1[1]" Path2="2[1].2[1].1[1]"/>
							<PathValue Operator="EQ" Path1="1[1].2[1].2[1]" Path2="2[1].2[1].2[1]"/>
							<PathValue Operator="EQ" Path1="1[1].2[1].3[1]" Path2="2[1].2[1].3[1]"/>
							<PathValue Operator="EQ" Path1="1[1].2[1].4[1]" Path2="2[1].2[1].4[1]"/>
						</FORALL>
					</Assertion>

conformanceStatements.description: The value of ORC-3 (Filler Order Number) SHALL be identical to the value of OBR-3 (Filler Order Number) within the same Order_Observation Group instance.
conformanceStatements.assertion:
<Assertion xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">
						<FORALL>
							<PathValue Operator="EQ" Path1="1[1].3[1].1[1]" Path2="2[1].3[1].1[1]"/>
							<PathValue Operator="EQ" Path1="1[1].3[1].2[1]" Path2="2[1].3[1].2[1]"/>
							<PathValue Operator="EQ" Path1="1[1].3[1].3[1]" Path2="2[1].3[1].3[1]"/>
							<PathValue Operator="EQ" Path1="1[1].3[1].4[1]" Path2="2[1].3[1].4[1]"/>
						</FORALL>
					</Assertion>

conformanceStatements.description: The value of ORC-12 (Ordering Provider) SHALL be identical to the value of OBR-16 (Ordering Provider) within the same Order_Observation Group instance.
The value of OBR-1 (Set ID - OBR) SHALL be valued sequentially starting with the value '1' across the Order_Observation Groups.

If there are multiple OBX segments associated with the same OBR segment that have the same OBX-3 (Observation Identifier) values for (OBX-3.1 (Identifier) + OBX-3.3 (Name of Coding System)) or (OBX-3.4 (Alternate Identifier) + OBX-3.6 (Name of Alternate Coding System)), a combination of (OBX-3.1 + OBX3.3) or (OBX-3.4 + OBX-3.6) and OBX-4 SHALL create a unique identification under a single OBR.

If one or more SPM segments are present for the same OBR, then the earliest SPM-17.1 (Range Start Date/Time) SHALL be equal to or before OBR-7 (Observation Date/Time) and OBR-7 (Observation Date/Time) SHALL be equal to or before the latest SPM-17.2 (Range End Date/Time).

If one or more SPM segments are present for the same OBR and if OBR-8 (Observation End Date/Time) is present, OBR-8 (Observation End Date/Time) SHALL be equal to or before the latest SPM-17.2 (Range End Date/Time).

Results with a Parent/Child relationship (as defined in Section 8.1 Parent/Child Reporting for Reflex and Culture/Susceptibility Testing), such as Microbiology and Reflex Results MUST provide proper linking from the Child result to the Parent OBR and OBX.

If OBR-26 (Parent Result) is valued, then there SHALL be at least one OBX in the message where OBX-3 (Observation Identifier) = OBR-26.1 (Parent Observation Identifier) AND OBX-4 (Observation Sub-ID) = OBR-26.2 (Parent Observation Sub-identifier)

If OBR-29 (Parent) is valued, then there SHALL be at least one other OBR in the message where OBR-2 (Placer Order Number) = OBR-29.1 (Placer Assigned Identifier) AND OBR-3 (Filler Order Number) = OBR-29.2 (Filler Assigned Identifier)

An occurrence of MSH-21 (Message Profile Identifier) SHALL be valued with '2.16.840.1.113883.9.195.3.3' (LRI_NG_FRU_Profile) or three occurrences SHALL be valued with '2.16.840.1.113883.9.16' (LRI_Common_Component), '2.16.840.1.113883.9.13' (LRI_NG_Component) and '2.16.840.1.113883.9.83' (LAB_FRU_Component) in any order.
conformanceStatements.assertion:
<Assertion xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">
						<OR>
							<PlainText AtLeastOnce="true" IgnoreCase="false" Path="1[1].21[*].3[1]" Text="2.16.840.1.113883.9.195.3.3"/>
							<FORALL>
								<PlainText AtLeastOnce="true" IgnoreCase="false" Path="1[1].21[*].3[1]" Text="2.16.840.1.113883.9.16"/>
								<PlainText AtLeastOnce="true" IgnoreCase="false" Path="1[1].21[*].3[1]" Text="2.16.840.1.113883.9.13"/>
								<PlainText AtLeastOnce="true" IgnoreCase="false" Path="1[1].21[*].3[1]" Text="2.16.840.1.113883.9.83"/>
							</FORALL>
						</OR>
					</Assertion>

conformanceStatements.description: The value of ORC-3 (Filler Order Number) SHALL NOT be valued identical to another instance of ORC-3 (Filler Order Number) in the same message excluding the Prior Result group(s).
The value of OBR-3 (Filler Order Number) SHALL NOT be valued identical to another instance of OBR-3 (Filler Order Number) in the message.

conformanceStatements.description: MSH-1 (Field Separator) SHALL contain the constant value '|'.
MSH-2 (Encoding Characters) SHALL contain the constant value '^~\&' or the constant value '^~\&#'.
conformanceStatements.assertion:
<Assertion xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">
						<AND>
							<Presence Path="2[1]"/>
							<OR>
								<PlainText IgnoreCase="false" Path="2[1]" Text="^~\&"/>
								<PlainText IgnoreCase="false" Path="2[1]" Text="^~\&#"/>
							</OR>
						</AND>
					</Assertion>

conformanceStatements.description: MSH-9.1 (Message Type.Message Code) SHALL contain the constant value 'ORU' drawn from the code systems HL70076.
MSH-9.2 (Message Type.Event Trigger) SHALL contain the constant value 'R01' drawn from the code systems HL70003.
MSH-9.3 (Message Type.Message Structure) SHALL contain the constant value 'ORU_R01' drawn from the code system HL70354.
MSH-12.1 (Version ID.Version ID) SHALL contain the constant value '2.5.1' drawn from code system HL70104.

predicates.description: If OBR-11 (Specimen Action Code) is valued "G".
If CWE_CRE.1 (Identifier) or CWE_CRE.4 (Alternate Identifier) of at least one occurrence of OBR-49 (Result Handling) is valued 'CC' or 'BCC'
predicates.assertion:
<Condition xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance">
						<AND>
							<!-- either OBR-49.1 or OBR-49.4 have to be present -->
							<OR>
								<Presence Path="49[*].1[1]"/>
								<Presence Path="49[*].4[1]"/>
							</OR>
							<!-- at least one occurrence of  OBR-49.1 must be valued 'CC' OR
									at least one occurrence of  OBR-49.1 must be valued 'BCC' OR
									at least one occurrence of  OBR-49.4 must be valued 'CC' OR
									at least one occurrence of  OBR-49.4 must be valued 'CC' OR-->
							<EXIST>
								<PlainText AtLeastOnce="true" IgnoreCase="false" Path="49[*].1[1]" Text="CC"/>
								<PlainText AtLeastOnce="true" IgnoreCase="false" Path="49[*].4[1]" Text="CC"/>
								<PlainText AtLeastOnce="true" IgnoreCase="false" Path="49[*].1[1]" Text="BCC"/>
								<PlainText AtLeastOnce="true" IgnoreCase="false" Path="49[*].4[1]" Text="BCC"/>
							</EXIST>
						</AND>
					</Condition>
